Lentil Split Pea Falafel, Radish Ribbons, Cucumber Bowl with Tahini Dressing

Falafels:
1/4 c lentils (any brown lentils, whole masoor or spanish brown)
1/4 c yellow or green split peas
2 c water
1/3 c chopped red onion
4 cloves garlic
1/4 packed cup cilantro
1/4 packed cup parsley
1/2-3/4 tsp salt to taste
1/2 tsp cumin powder
1/2 tsp whole coriander seeds or coriander powder
14-1/2 tsp cayenne pepper/ or black pepper (can also add 1/2 of a serano chili pepper_
2 tsp oil (optional)
1 tbsp sesame seeds
1-2 tbsp chickpea flour

Wash the lentils and split peas. Drain, add to a deep pan with 2 c of water. Cook on medium high heat for 18-19 min. (15min if they were pre-soaked for 30 min). Drain and cool slightly. Add to a food processor. Add all the ingredients except chickpea flour and pulse to make a coarse mixture. Transfer to a bowl. Add flour as needed to make the dough less sticky. If the dough is too sticky, chill for a few minutes. Preheat oven to 400F. Grease hands and shape the dough into 1-1.5" balls. Place on parchment lined sheet. Brush oil on top and bake for 20 min or until golden crisp on the outside.

Dressing:
1/3 c tahini
1 clove garlic
2 tsp fresh parsley or 1/2 tsp dried
2-3 tbsp lemon juice
1 tbsp evoo
3-4 tbsp water
1/4 tsp salt
generous dash of cayenne and black pepper

Blend everything together. Taste and adjust tang and salt. Add more lemon juice if needed.


Daikon made into ribbons with a peeler
cucumber slices
torn lettuce
pickles (optional)
cilantro and sesame seeds for garnish

Assemble the bowl with lettuce, cucumbers, radish ribbons, and other veggies. Drizzle a generous amount of tahini dressing. Serve with warm falafels and garnish with black and white sesame seeds and cilantro. 

The falafels can be stored for up to 3 days in the refrigerator.
